item.thebetweenlands.elixir.basilisk_eff: Petrifies the motor cortex of the brain, causing one to be frozen in place.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.blindman_eff: Severely limits the function of the eye, causing one to only be able to see a small distance in front of them and be unable to sprint.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.cats_eyes_ef: Makes the eyes extremely sensitive to light, allowing one to see very well in the dark.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.decay_effect: Increases vulnerability to the decaying aura of the Betweenlands, causing one to experience a quicker decline in physical and psychological health.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.drunkard_eff: Causes one to experience a heavy bout of nausea.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.feasting_eff: Gives the stomach something tough to feed on, satisfying one's hunger over time.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.fogged_mind_: Clouds the mind with worrisome thoughts, causing one to see the illusion of a thick fog surrounding them.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.healing_effe: Accelerates natural regeneration, healing one's wounds over time.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.heavyweight_: Gives a strange sense of heaviness, causing one to find swimming more difficult and causing them to sink in Mud despite whatever they may be wearing to protect them from it.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.hunter_sense: Enhances the senses, allowing one to see and smell the scent trails of creatures in order to track them down.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.lightweight_: Causes a strange sensation of weightlessness, allowing one to walk slowly over water as if it were solid ground.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.lumbering_ef: Makes the muscles lethargic, reducing one's movement speed.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.masking_effe: Masks natural odors like a perfume, making it harder for one to be detected by predators.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.nimblefeet_e: Enhances muscle swiftness and nimbleness, increasing one's movement speed.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.poisonsting_: Contains the wrath of the sinister plants found in the Betweenlands, poisoning one instantly.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.ripening_eff: Reverses the effects of the decaying aura of the Betweenlands, restoring one's physical and psychological health over time.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.sagittarius_: Contains the power of Sagittarius, allowing one to see exactly what path their arrow will take when fired from a bow.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.slugarm_effe: Makes the arms feel numb, decreasing one's arm swinging speed and thus causing them to mine slower and strike foes less easily.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.spiderbreed_: Changes the workings of the skin and muscle, allowing one to climb up and down any obstacle as if they were an insect.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.starvation_e: Makes the stomach digest food faster and less efficiently, causing one to go hungry more quickly.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.stenching_ef: Causes the emission of a very potent odor that is desired by monsters, making it easier for one to be detected by predators.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.strength_eff: Increases raw physical strength, causing one to deal more damage when they attack.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.swiftarm_eff: Enables arm muscles to work to their fullest, increasing one's arm swinging speed and thus allowing them to mine faster, pull back bows more rapidly, and strike foes more easily.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.toughskin_ef: Increases skin toughness, protecting one from harmful plants found throughout the Betweenlands.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.unclouded_ef: Clears a foggy mind, allowing one to see through dense fog as if it evaporated in front of their eyes.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.weakbow_effe: Reduces archery skill, greatly limiting one's bow shooting range.
item.thebetweenlands.elixir.weakness_eff: Weakens the muscles, reducing one's damage output when they attack.

manual.thebetweenlands.herblore.has_aspe: This item has the following aspects:
manual.thebetweenlands.herblore.thebetwe: The aspect that influences the desire of a being or a thought.<nl>Tier II aspect.
The aspect that has effect on the muscles.<nl>Tier I aspect.

<scale:0.75>The Basilisk Draught petrifies the motor cortex of the brain, causing one to be frozen in place. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Fergalaz, Dayuniis, Yihinren, Yunugaz, and Byariis aspects is required to make this draught. <nl>The more Azuwynn is used, the stronger are the draught’s effects. The more Yihinren is used, the longer the draught lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the draught, turning it into the Spiderbreed Draught, which allows one to climb on obstacles.</scale>

<scale:0.75>The Blindman’s Brew severely limits the functions of the eye, causing one to only be able to see a small distance in front of them and be unable to sprint. <nl>A combination of Freiwynn, Dayuniis, Ordaniis, Geoliirgaz, and Byariis aspects is required to make this brew. <nl>The more Freiwynn is used, the stronger are the brew's effects. The more Dayuniis is used, the longer the brew lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the brew, turning it into the Brew of the Cat’s Eye, which allows one to see better in the dark.</scale>
The aspect that changes the nature of anything to its opposite.<nl>Tier I special aspect.
The aspect that correlates to the element of water.<nl>Tier II aspect.

<scale:0.8>The Brew of the Cat's Eye makes the eyes extremely sensitive to light, allowing one to see very well in the dark. <nl>A combination of Freiwynn, Dayuniis, Ordaniis, and Geoliirgaz aspects is required to make this brew. <nl>The more Freiwynn is used, the stronger are the brew's effects. The more Dayuniis is used, the longer the brew lasts. <nl>Adding Byariis will corrupt the nature of the brew, turning it into the Blindman's Brew, which causes one to be blinded.</scale>
The aspect that influences the digestive organs and immune system.<nl>Tier I aspect.
The aspect that has effect on the mind and the border between reality and imagination.<nl>Tier II aspect.

<scale:0.75>The Elixir of Decay increases vulnerability to the decaying aura of the Betweenlands, causing one to experience a quicker decline in physical and psychological health. <nl>A combination of Yeowynn, Ordaniis, Dayuniis, and Byariis aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Dayuniis is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. The more Ordaniis is used, the longer the elixir lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the elixir, turning it into the Elixir of Ripening, which reverses one's responses to the decaying aura.</scale>

<scale:0.85>The Elixir of Draining eats away at the body, draining one's health over time. <nl>A combination of Yeowynn, Ordaniis, and Byariis aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Yeowynn is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. The more Ordaniis is used, the longer the elixir lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the elixir, turning it into the Elixir of Healing, which restores one's health over time.</scale>

<scale:0.75>The Drunkard’s Brew is highly intoxicating, causing one to experience a heavy bout of nausea. <nl>A combination of Freiwynn, Dayuniis, Ordaniis, Firnalaz, and Byariis aspects is required to make this brew. <nl>The more Freiwynn is used, the stronger are the brew’s effects. The more Dayuniis is used, the longer the brew lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the brew, turning it into the Hunter’s Sense Brew, which allows one to detect the scent trails of creatures.</scale>

<scale:0.8>The Elixir of Feasting gives the stomach something tough to feed on, satisfying one's hunger over time. <nl>A combination of Yeowynn, Ordaniis, and Celawynn aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Celawynn is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. The more Ordaniis is used, the longer the elixir lasts. <nl>Adding Byariis will corrupt the nature of the elixir, turning it into the Elixir of Starvation, which causes one to go hungry more quickly.</scale>
The aspect that correlates to the element of earth.<nl>Tier II aspect.
The aspect that correlates to the element of fire.<nl>Tier II aspect.

<scale:0.75>The Draught of the Fogged Mind clouds the mind with worrisome thoughts, causing one to see the illusion of a thick fog surrounding them. <nl>A combination of Dayuniis, Freiwynn, Geoliirgaz, Ordaniis, Yunugaz, and Byariis aspects is required to make this draught. <nl>The more Geoliirgaz is used, the stronger are the draught's effects. The more Dayuniis is used, the longer the draught lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the draught, turning it into the Draught of the Unclouded, which causes any fog to be cleared from one's vision.</scale>
The aspect that has effect on the perception of light.<nl>Tier II aspect.
The aspect that correlates to the formless element of void or ether.<nl>Tier III aspect.
Large patches of Algae can be found quite commonly in any biome on the surface of the water.
Angler Teeth are dropped by Anglers, which can be found lurking in the murky waters of The Betweenlands.
Aqua Middle Gems are one of three Middle Gem types that can be found stuck in Mud.
Arrow Arum is a leafy plant that grows in the wet Marsh biomes of The Betweenlands.
Blackhat Mushrooms can be found scattered about everywhere in Swamplands biomes.
Bladderworts are tall underwater plants that grow in Deep Waters biomes and more rarely in Coarse Islands biomes.
The stalk of the Bladderwort plant that grows in Deep Waters and Coarse Islands biomes.
Blue Eyed Grass is a plant with tiny blue flowers that can be found in the Patchy Islands biome.
Blue Iris is one of the two iris plants found growing in the Coarse Islands biome.
Found in the Patchy Islands biome, Bog Bean grows on Mud in shallow water.
Boneset is a flower that grows in the Patchy Islands biome.
Bottlebrush Grass is a small plant that grows in Marsh biomes.
Broomsedges are tall plants that can be found in Marsh biomes.

<scale:0.8>Bulb-Capped Mushrooms are luminous bright blue mushrooms that can be found growing around Giant Bulb-Capped Mushrooms in Patchy Islands biomes, and in Underground Oases. They have been known to cause minor trips.</scale>
Button Bushes are small plants that grow in Marsh biomes.
Cardinal Flowers are tall bright red plants that grow in the Patchy Islands biome.
Cattails are very common plants that grow in Swamplands, Patchy Islands, and Coarse Islands biomes.
Cave Grass grows deep underground in the Pitstone layer, away from the light.
Cave Moss can be found growing down underground in caves.
Copper Iris is one of the two iris plants found growing in the Coarse Islands biome.
Crimson Middle Gems are one of three Middle Gem types that can be found stuck in Mud.
Crimson Snail Shells are dropped by Blood Snails, which are found in Swamplands and Patchy Islands biomes.
Cryptweed is a mysterious hanging plant that grows in the Sludgeon vaults. It contains strange properties.
Deep Water Coral is a blue luminous aquatic plant that grows in Mud in Deep Waters biomes.
Swamp Reeds grow in the water in Patchy Islands and Coarse Islands biomes, and on land in Swamplands biomes.
Edge Leaves are small plants that grow on edges in the Sludgeon vaults. They contain strange properties.
Edge Moss is a plant that grows on edges in the Sludgeon vaults. It contains strange properties.
Edge Shrooms are fungi that grow on edges in the Sludgeon vaults. They contain strange properties.
Flathead Mushrooms grow very commonly in the Swamplands biome.
Golden Clubs are strange orange flowers that grow in water in the Patchy Islands biome.
Green Middle Gems are one of three Middle Gem types that can be found stuck in Mud.
Hangers are vine-like plants that grow off of Giant Weedwood and Hearthgrove Trees, Giant Roots, and down from caves.
Leaves are dropped by the small leafy Swamp Plants that grow in Swamplands biomes, as well as from the Fallen Leaves that gather under trees there.
<scale:0.9>Lichen is a plant can be found growing on Cragrock Spires in the Deep Waters biome, and also sometimes underground or on stone based structures.</scale>
The Marsh Hibiscus is a pretty looking flower that grows in the Marsh biome.
Marsh Mallows are small pink and white flowers that can be found in Marsh biomes. Quite contrary to their name, they don't taste particularly nice.
Marsh Marigolds are yellow flowers that grow in water in the Patchy Islands biome.
Milkweed is a bright pink flower that grows in the Patchy Islands biome.
Mire Coral is an orange luminous aquatic plant that grows in Mud in Deep Waters, Patchy Islands, and Coarse Islands biomes.
Moss is a plant that grows and spreads around almost anywhere.
Nettles can be found in Coarse Islands, Marsh and Swamplands biomes. They will sting you if you touch them, so be careful.
Ochre Snail Shells are dropped by Mire Snails, which are found in Swamplands and Patchy Islands biomes.
Pale Grass is a transparent, ghostly grass found in the Sludgeon vaults. It contains strange properties.
Phragmites are tall plants that grow everywhere in Marsh biomes.
Pickerelweed is a flower that can be found in Marsh biomes.
Pitchers are large plants that grow in Swamplands biomes.
Poison Ivy is a poisonous hanging plant that grows commonly on small Weedwood and Nibbletwig Trees.
<scale:0.8>Roots grow in Coarse Islands and Sludge Plains biomes, in both regular and Giant forms. They can also be derived from Pyrads, nature spirits found around Giant Weedwood Trees.</scale>
Rotbulbs are disgusting growths found in the Sludgeon vaults. They contain strange properties.
Shoots are small young plants found growing in the Patchy Islands biome.
Sludgecreep is a slime-feeding plant found in the Sludge Plains biome, including in the Sludgeon vaults.
Soft Rush is a small plant that grows in the Marsh biome.
String Roots hang from the ceiling of the Sludgeon vaults. They contain strange properties.
Sundews are large plants that grow in Marsh biomes.
Swamp Grass is a common plant found in Swamplands, Patchy Islands, Coarse Islands, and Marsh biomes, and in Underground Oases.
Swamp Kelp is an aquatic plant that grows commonly in Deep Waters and Coarse Islands biomes.
Thorns are dangerous hanging plants that grow deep down underground in caves.
Venus Fly Traps are small plants that grow in Swamplands biomes.
Volarpads are very large plants that grow commonly in Coarse Islands biomes and sometimes in Swamplands biomes.
Water Weeds can be found growing in Mud at the bottom of the water in Deep Waters biomes.
<scale:0.9>Weedwood Bark grows around the soft wood inside Weedwood Trees. It can also be derived from the Hollow Logs found scattered about Swamplands, Marsh, and Sludge Plains biomes.</scale>

<scale:0.85>The Elixir of Healing accelerates natural regeneration, healing one's wounds over time. <nl>A combination of Yeowynn and Ordaniis aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Yeowynn is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. The more Ordaniis is used, the longer the elixir lasts. <nl>Adding Byariis will corrupt the nature of the elixir, turning it into the Elixir of Draining, which drains one's health over time.</scale>

<scale:0.75>The Heavyweight Draught gives a strange sense of heaviness, causing one to find swimming more difficult and causing them to sink in Mud despite whatever they may be wearing to protect them from it. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Byrginaz, Yunugaz, Yihinren, Geoliirgaz, and Byariis aspects is required to make this draught. <nl>The more Yunugaz is used, the stronger are the draught’s effects. The more Yihinren is used, the longer the draught lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the draught, turning it into the Lightweight Draught, which allows one to walk over water.</scale>

<scale:0.8>The Hunter’s Sense Brew enhances the senses, allowing one to see and smell the scent trails of creatures in order to track them down. <nl>A combination of Freiwynn, Dayuniis, Ordaniis, and Firnalaz aspects is required to make this brew. <nl>The more Freiwynn is used, the stronger are the brew’s effects. The more Dayuniis is used, the longer the brew lasts. <nl>Adding Byariis will corrupt the nature of the brew, turning it into the Drunkard’s Brew, which causes one to experience heavy nausea.</scale>

<scale:0.75>The Lightweight Draught causes a strange sensation of weightlessness, allowing one to walk slowly over water as if it were solid ground. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Byrginaz, Yunugaz, Yihinren, and Geoliirgaz aspects is required to make this draught. <nl>The more Yunugaz is used, the stronger are the draught’s effects. The more Yihinren is used, the longer the draught lasts. <nl>Adding Byariis will corrupt the nature of the draught, turning it into the Heavyweight Draught, which hinders one's swimming ability and causes them to sink in Mud no matter what they are wearing to counteract it.</scale>

<scale:0.85>The Lumbering Elixir makes the muscles lethargic, reducing one's movement speed. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Ordaniis, Yunugaz, and Byariis aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Yunugaz is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. The more Ordaniis is used, the longer the elixir lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the elixir, turning it into the Nimblefeet Elixir, which speeds one's movement.</scale>

<scale:0.8>The Masking Brew masks natural odors like a perfume, making it harder for one to be detected by predators. <nl>A combination of Dayuniis, Armaniis, and Byariis aspects is required to make this brew. <nl>The more Armaniis is used, the stronger are the brew’s effects. The more Dayuniis is used, the longer the brew lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the brew, turning it into the Stenching Brew, which makes it easier for one to be detected by predators.</scale>

<scale:0.85>The Nimblefeet Elixir enhances muscle swiftness and nimbleness, increasing one's movement speed. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Ordaniis, and Yunugaz aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Yunugaz is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. The more Ordaniis is used, the longer the elixir lasts. <nl>Adding Byariis will corrupt the nature of the elixir, turning it into the Lumbering Elixir, which slows one's movement.</scale>
The aspect that activates other aspects or enhances power in any form.<nl>Tier I aspect.

<scale:0.8>The Poisonsting Elixir contains the wrath of the sinister plants found in the Betweenlands, poisoning one instantly. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Yeowynn, Celawynn, and Byariis aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Yeowynn is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. The more Celawynn is used, the longer the elixir lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the elixir, turning it into the Toughskin Elixir, which protects one from harmful plants.</scale>

<scale:0.75>The Elixir of Ripening reverses the effects of the decaying aura of the Betweenlands, restoring one's physical and psychological health over time. <nl>A combination of Yeowynn, Ordaniis, and Dayuniis aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Dayuniis is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. The more Ordaniis is used, the longer the elixir lasts. <nl>Adding Byariis will corrupt the nature of the elixir, turning it into the Elixir of Decay, which accelerates one's vulnerability to the decaying aura’s effects.</scale>

<scale:0.75>The Draught of Sagittarius contains the power of Sagittarius, allowing one to see exactly what path their arrow will take when fired from a bow. <nl>A combination of Freiwynn, Dayuniis, Byariis, Ordaniis, and Armaniis aspects is required to make this draught. <nl>The more Freiwynn is used, the stronger are the draught's effects. Sap Spit is a tacky secretion produced by Spirit Trees. It seems to have regenerative properties.

<scale:0.75>The Slugarm Brew makes the arms feel numb, decreasing one's arm swinging speed and thus causing them to mine slower and strike foes less easily. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Dayuniis, Yunugaz, Ordaniis, and Byariis aspects is required to make this brew. <nl>The more Azuwynn is used, the stronger are the brew’s effects. The more Ordaniis is used, the longer the brew lasts. <nl>Leaving out Byariis will reveal the true nature of the brew, turning it into the Swiftarm Brew, which increases one's arm swinging speed.</scale>

<scale:0.75>The Spiderbreed Draught changes the workings of the skin and muscle, allowing one to climb up and down any obstacle as if they were an insect. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Fergalaz, Dayuniis, Yihinren, and Yunugaz aspects is required to make this draught. <nl>The more Azuwynn is used, the stronger are the draught’s effects. The more Yihinren is used, the longer the draught lasts. <nl>Adding Byariis will corrupt the nature of the draught, turning it into the Basilisk Draught, which causes one to experience paralysis.</scale>

<scale:0.8>The Elixir of Starvation makes the stomach digest food faster and less efficiently, causing one to go hungry more quickly. <nl>A combination of Yeowynn, Ordaniis, Celawynn, and Byariis aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Celawynn is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. <scale:0.8>The Stenching Brew has a very potent odor that is desired by monsters, making it easier for one to be detected by predators. <nl>A combination of Dayuniis and Armaniis aspects is required to make this brew. <nl>The more Armaniis is used, the stronger are the brew’s effects. <scale:0.8>The Elixir of Strength increases raw physical strength, causing one to deal more damage when they attack. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn and Ordaniis aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Azuwynn is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. <scale:0.75>The Swiftarm Brew enables arm muscles to work to their fullest, increasing one's arm swinging speed and thus allowing them to mine faster, pull back bows more rapidly, and strike foes more easily. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Dayuniis, Yunugaz, and Ordaniis aspects is required to make this brew. <nl>The more Azuwynn is used, the stronger are the brew’s effects. <scale:0.8>The Toughskin Elixir increases skin toughness, protecting one from harmful plants found throughout the Betweenlands. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Yeowynn, and Celawynn aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Yeowynn is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects. The aspect that correlates to the natural orderless state of the universe.<nl>Tier III aspect.

<scale:0.75>The Draught of the Unclouded clears a foggy mind, allowing one to see through dense fog as if it evaporated in front of their eyes. <nl>A combination of Dayuniis, Freiwynn, Geoliirgaz, Ordaniis, and Yunugaz aspects is required to make this draught. <nl>The more Geoliirgaz is used, the stronger are the draught's effects. <scale:0.8>The Elixir of Weakness weakens the muscles, reducing one's damage output when they attack. <nl>A combination of Azuwynn, Ordaniis, and Byariis aspects is required to make this elixir. <nl>The more Azuwynn is used, the stronger are the elixir’s effects.
